<1ST_LINE>u i AM-Japan-Markets 2ndLd-Writethru   09-19 0200</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Japan-Markets, 2nd Ld-Writethru,a0401,0204</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Stocks Up</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Leads with 3 grafs to UPDATE with Nikkei and dollar closings.
Pick up 4th pvs, The rate.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Both share prices and the dollar inched up during
Tokyo trading Monday.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues, a 60.71-point
winner last Friday, finished trading at 27,901.00, up 34.62 points
or 0.12 percent.
   The dollar closed at 133.80 yen, up 0.04 yen from last week's
close of 133.76 yen. The currency fluctuated between 133.75 yen and
134.10 yen after opening the day at 134.00 yen.
   ``The rate was not moving at all,'' said a foreign exchange
dealer with Mitsubishi Bank.
   He added that only a few individuals were participating in the
market. ``Investors are sort of waiting on the sidelines after a
series of market-affecting news and they don't expect the dollar to
rise further,'' he said, speaking on condition of anonymity.
   On the stock market, ``trading was pretty active for a Monday,
led by steels and shipbuildings issues,'' said an analyst with
Nomura Securities, Japan's largest brokerage.
   Strong share prices in Tokyo reflected higher closing rates in
overseas markets last week, the analyst added, speaking on
condition of anonymity.
</TEXT>
