<2ND_LINE>PM-South Africa-Bomb,0182</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Car Bomb Explodes Under Apartment Building</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A stolen car loaded with
limpet mines exploded today in a garage under an apartment
building, injuring a 6-year-old boy and damaging more than 30 cars,
police said.
   They said the explosion also shattered windows in the four-story
building about 300 feet from the police station in Benoni, 18 miles
east of Johannesburg.
   The child was cut by flying glass and several people were
treated for shock, police said.
   They said the pre-dawn blast was one of the most powerful of
more than 40 bombings in South Africa this year.
   Authorities have blamed most of the previous bombings on the
outlawed African National Congress, the main guerrilla movement
fighting the South African government and its policy of apartheid.
The ANC acknowledges waging a bombing and sabotage campaign, but
generally does not comment on individual incidents.
   Apartheid establishes a racially segregated society in which the
26 million blacks have no vote in national affairs, which are
controlled by 5 million whites.
</TEXT>
