<2ND_LINE>PM-Dukakis-Health, 1st Ld-Writethru,170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dukakis Health Excellent Except For Back Pain, Doctor Says</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS 1st graf to restore AP logo after dateline.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Democratic nominee Michael Dukakis is in excellent
health except for an occasional backache, his doctor said today.
   A medical statement was issued by Dr. Gerald Plotkin as Dukakis
flew to Little Rock, Ark., and Houston for campaign appearances.
Plotkin said campaign travel made Dukakis' back pain worsen.
   Dukakis had a routine medical checkup Sept. 10 at the Harvard
Community Health Plan's Wellesley Center and ``was found to be in
excellent health,'' Plotkin said.
   ``Over the last eight to 10 months he has had intermittent,
nagging low back discomfort exacerbated by long periods of sitting
in airplanes,'' the doctor said.
   He said Dukakis takes an anti-inflammatory medication to ease
the back pain.
   On Aug. 3, the candidate's longtime doctor issued a detailed,
three-page statement which said Dukakis had only received treatment
for routine ailments, such as hay fever and muscle sprains, and
``has had no psychological symptoms, complaints or treatment.''
   ``He has had no significant illnesses during his lifetime and
has been in excellent health,'' Plotkin said then. ``He has never
appeared depressed to me.''
