<TEXT>
   A policeman who killed a man last month was in
custody Monday, charged with sexual battery on a prostitute,
authorities said.
   Efrain Grillo, 23, was arrested Sunday after the 29-year-old
woman filed a complaint with police. He was jailed without bond.
   Grillo's partner, Daryl Branton, 24, was relieved of duty with
pay pending an investigation, said Miami police spokesman David
Rivero.
   Last month, Grillo fatally shot a street window washer after an
altercation, but the slaying was ruled justifiable after the
officer said the victim pulled a knife on him.
   In the latest incident, Grillo and Branton, both in uniform,
allegedly ordered the woman into the back of the patrol car. She
later told police she thought she was being arrested.
   They drove to a nearby abandoned building and Grillo ordered the
woman out of the car, according to the complaint. He then fondled
her, at one point putting on a rubber glove, the police report
said. Branton allegedly watched but did not participate.
