<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF-Netherlands-NATO     09-19 0113</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF-Netherlands-NATO,0117</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dutch Army Withdraws 500 Soldiers From NATO Maneuver</HEAD>
<DATELINE>THE HAGUE, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Dutch army withdrew 500
soldiers on Monday from a NATO maneuver in West Germany after one
of the unit's members died of meningitis, an army spokesman said.
   Another soldier from the 107th Field Artillery Unit was
hospitalized with suspected meningitis Monday but was reported in
satisfactory condition, according to the spokesman, who spoke on
condition of anonymity.
   The 500 soldiers, part of a 34,000-strong Dutch contingent at
the Free Lion maneuver, will all undergo medical checks, the
spokesman said.
   Other nations participating in the 45,000-member Free Lion force
are West Germany, Britain and the United States.
</TEXT>
