<HEAD>Nebraskans Favor Bush in Presidential Race</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OMAHA, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Forty-four percent of Nebraskans support
Republican George Bush for president and 33 percent would vote for
Democrat Michael Dukakis in November, according to a poll published
Monday.
   Twenty-three percent of the 755 registered Nebraska voters
surveyed in the Omaha World-Herald poll said they were undecided.
   The margin of error in the telephone poll, conducted Sept. 14-15
by SRI Research Inc., is plus or minus 3.6 percentage points.
