<DATELINE>LITTLE ROCK, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Democratic presidential nominee Michael
Dukakis jokingly said Monday that he urged Arkansas Gov. Bill
Clinton to give the long nominating speech that drew criticism at
the Democratic National Convention.
   Clinton, introducing Dukakis at a campaign rally in Little Rock,
spoke more briefly than he did in nominating the Massachusetts
governor in Atlanta.
   He won applause and laughter with his ``in conclusion'' sign-off.
