speech.
   ``I read Bill's nominating speech,'' said Dukakis. ``I thought
it was pretty good and I urged him to deliver it. Of course, we had
a little deal going with Johnny Carson.''
   Clinton appeared as a guest on Carson's late night television
program after convention delegates complained that the Arkansas
governor's address had lasted too long.
