<1ST_LINE>r p AM-BRF--OhioPoll     09-19 0130</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Ohio Poll,120</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dukakis Support Slides Among Ohio Voters</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vice President George Bush, who once trailed
Michael Dukakis by 10 percentage points in Ohio, is in a dead heat
with the Democratic nominee, according to a new poll of state
voters.
   Among 667 Ohio registered voters, 43 percent support Bush, 39
percent favor Dukakis and 18 percent are undecided, the University
of Akron poll said. The 4 percentage point margin of error means
the race is a statistical dead heat.
   Since last April, Dukakis has dropped 5 points, Bush has risen 9
points and the number of undecided voters declined 4 points.
   The poll, commissioned by The (Akron) Beacon Journal, WKYC-TV in
Cleveland and WCMH-TV in Columbus, was conducted between Sept. 6-15
and published Sunday.
</TEXT>
