<HEAD>`China Beach' Wins Delayed Emmy Award</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   It took an extra three weeks, but ABC
received another Emmy Award for its series ``China Beach.''
   Presentation of the trophy, awarded to the ABC drama program for
best costuming, was delayed when it was learned that the Emmy
judging panel had not seen one of the programs nominated for
costuming in its entirety.
   The statuette was to be handed out on Aug. 27 during the
non-televised Emmy ceremony. Announcement of the Emmy win was made
Monday.
   Given to costumers Paul Kaatz and Darryl Levine, the award
brings ABC's total Emmy count to 22. ABC emerged from the televised
awards program on Aug. 28 with 21 trophies, most among the three
networks.
