<HEAD>Czechoslovak Defector Soars To Austria With Hang Glider</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 42-year-old Czechoslovak used a hang
glider Monday to flee the country by soaring over the Austrian
border, police said.
   The craft, which had a small motor, flew 31 miles from the
Slovakian city of Breclav to the eastern Austria city of Sierndorf,
about three miles inside the border, Austrian authorities said.
   Police identified the man only as Jiri R. He could have made it
to Austria by flying only six miles, but he told reporters that he
lost his bearings in an early morning fog.
   He was transferred to the Traiskirchen refugee camp south of
Vienna, authorities said.
</TEXT>
