<HEAD>Toddler Abandoned in Apartment After Apparent Murder-Suicide of
Parents</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CENTREVILLE, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 17-month-old boy wandered around an
apartment alone after his father apparently shot and killed his
mother and then himself in the residence in this Washington suburb,
police said Monday.
   The bodies of the unidentified couple, who apparently were
estranged, were found about 1:45 p.m. by a neighbor at the Bent
Tree Circle residence, said Fairfax County police spokesman Peter
Fakoury.
   It was not immediately known how long the couple had been dead,
but police estimated the shooting occurred during the weekend. They
were believed to be in their 20s.
   The boy was unharmed but was taken to Fair Oaks Hospital,
Fakoury said. The child has been placed in the custody of the
county department of social services.
   The names were withheld pending positive identification and
notification of next of kin.
