<TEXT>
   The Senate is taking final action on plans to
phase out tariffs between the United States and Canada and end a
variety of other trade barriers.
   ``I consider this the most significant economic agreement the
United States has ever entered into with another country,'' said
Sen. Bob Packwood, R-Ore., a leading supporter.
   All tariffs between the two countries would be phased out over
10 years under the agreement, which was signed Jan. 2 by President
