<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The percentage of American households in which
the people who live together are related _ by marriage or otherwise
_ has declined a fifth in the last 40 years, the Census Bureau said
Monday.
   Families now constitute 71.5 percent of all households, down
from 90.3 percent in 1948, according to new figures, which also
showed the makeup of families continuing to change.
   The number of families without children at home exceeds the
number of those with children at home by an even greater margin
than four years ago, when those without children edged ahead for
the first time.
