nation's trade deficit for July as imports slowed.
   Most analysts agree that the recent slackening in the pace of
business activity has at least postponed any further moves by the
Federal Reserve to tighten credit.
   But some argue that the central bank will have to take further
steps sooner or later in its avowed mission to keep inflationary
pressures from reviving.
