<HEAD>London Stocks Slip</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with close.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices on the London Stock Exchange fell during a
subdued session Monday, with little corporate or economic news to
influence trading.
   Dealers said Wall Street's slide pulled London equities somewhat
lower in the last hour of trading.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index closed down
6.8 points, or 0.4 percent, at 1,759.9.
   Volume was modest, as 326.7 million shares changed hands,
compared with 396.5 million shares traded Friday.
   The Dow Jones industrial average was off 27.20 points at
2,070.95 as London trading subsided. British equities were able to
shake off most of Wall Street's slide as speculative situations
supported London prices, traders said.
   Traders also said players appeared hesitant to commit themselves
ahead of Tuesday's release of British money supply data for August.
</TEXT>
