<HEAD>Apple Extends Macintosh II Line With Macintosh IIx</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Apple Computer Inc. announced Monday a new
version of its Macintosh II called the Macintosh IIx, which it said
runs 10 percent to 15 percent faster.
   Even though the new computer uses a different microprocessor _
Motorola Inc.'s 68030 microprocessor instead of the older 68020 _
