<1ST_LINE>r f BC-IC-NameChange     09-19 0191</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-IC-Name Change,0198</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>IC Industries Will Become Whitman Corp.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   IC Industries Inc. will change its name to
Whitman Corp. on Dec. 1, as part of its evolution from railroad
operator to manufacturer of consumer goods and provider of
services, officials said Monday.
   The company's current name was derived from the initials of the
Illinois Central Railroad, which IC is spinning off to its
shareholders. The new name comes from Whitman's chocolates and
frozen desserts, one of the brands of Pet Inc., IC's foods
subsidiary.
   Chicago-based IC also owns Pepsi-Cola General Bottlers; Hussman
Corp., a manufacturer of food-service equipment; and auto-repair
specialist Midas International.
   ``The decision to change our name to Whitman Corp. is another
key step in our strategic plan to sharpen our focus on consumer
goods and service,'' Karl Bays, chairman and chief executive
officer, said in a statement.
   Spokesman Charles Connolly said the company settled on Whitman
as its new name after a year of research that gave it high marks
for familiarity, quality and distinction.
   ``It's easy to say, it's easy to spell, it tests very well and
it's ours to use,'' he said.
</TEXT>
